# Plan: Add `image-text-to-text` Pipeline to Transformers.js

## Context

Transformers.js supports many pipeline types, but is missing a first-class pipeline for
vision-language models (VLMs) that accept both an image *and* a text prompt to produce
generated text. The infrastructure already exists:

- `AutoModelForImageTextToText` is fully defined in `src/models.js` (line 8736), mapping
  LLaVA, PaliGemma, SmolVLM, Qwen2-VL, IDEFICS3, Florence2, etc.
- `AutoModelForImageTextToText` is already publicly exported (via `export * from './models.js'`
  in `src/transformers.js`).
- VLM processors (LLaVA, PaliGemma, etc.) accept `(images, text)` in a single `processor()`
  call and return `{ pixel_values, input_ids, attention_mask, ... }` — exactly what
  `model.generate()` needs.

The only work needed is in **`src/pipelines.js`** (new import, new class, new task entry,
updated JSDoc) and a **new test file**.

---

## Critical Files

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `src/pipelines.js` | All pipeline classes and SUPPORTED_TASKS mapping — **primary change file** |
| `src/models.js` | `AutoModelForImageTextToText` already defined at line 8736 |
| `src/transformers.js` | Re-exports everything — **no change needed** |
| `tests/pipelines/test_pipelines_image_text_to_text.js` | New test file (auto-discovered) |

---

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1 — Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to imports in `src/pipelines.js`

At the top of `src/pipelines.js` (lines 16–45), the file imports Auto* model classes from
`./models.js`. Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to the existing import block:

```js
// Existing last entry in the import block (line ~44):
    AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction,
    PreTrainedModel,
} from './models.js';
```

Change to:

```js
    AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction,
    AutoModelForImageTextToText,  // ← add this line
    PreTrainedModel,
} from './models.js';
```

---

### Step 2 — Add JSDoc typedefs before the new class

Immediately before the new class definition, add the three standard typedef blocks that
every pipeline uses (matching the pattern at lines 1943–1953 for `ImageToTextPipeline`):

```js
/**
 * @typedef {Object} ImageTextToTextSingle
 * @property {string} generated_text The generated text.
 * @typedef {ImageTextToTextSingle[]} ImageTextToTextOutput
 *
 * @callback ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback Process an image and a text prompt, generating text.
 * @param {ImageInput} image The image to be processed.
 * @param {string} text The text prompt for the model.
 * @param {Partial<import('./generation/configuration_utils.js').GenerationConfig>} [options] Additional keyword arguments to pass along to the generate method of the model.
 * @returns {Promise<ImageTextToTextOutput>} An object containing the generated text.
 *
 * @typedef {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs & ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback & Disposable} ImageTextToTextPipelineType
 */
```

---

### Step 3 — Add the `ImageTextToTextPipeline` class

Add the new class after the `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline` class (after line 2779) and
before the `VocoderOptions` typedef (line 2782). Follow the exact pattern of
`DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline`:

```js
/**
 * Image text to text pipeline using `AutoModelForImageTextToText`. This pipeline generates
 * text based on an image and a text prompt.
 *
 * **Example:** Generate text from an image and prompt w/ `onnx-community/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct`.
 * ```javascript
 * const pipe = await pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'onnx-community/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct');
 * const url = 'https://huggingface.co/datasets/Xenova/transformers.js-docs/resolve/main/cats.jpg';
 * const messages = [
 *   { role: 'user', content: [{ type: 'image' }, { type: 'text', text: 'Describe this image.' }] }
 * ];
 * const output = await pipe(url, messages);
 * // [{ generated_text: '...' }]
 * ```
 */
export class ImageTextToTextPipeline extends (/** @type {new (options: TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs) => ImageTextToTextPipelineType} */ (Pipeline)) {

    /**
     * Create a new ImageTextToTextPipeline.
     * @param {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs} options An object used to instantiate the pipeline.
     */
    constructor(options) {
        super(options);
    }

    /** @type {ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback} */
    async _call(image, text, generate_kwargs = {}) {

        // NOTE: For now, we only support a batch size of 1

        // Preprocess image
        const preparedImages = await prepareImages(image);

        // Process image and text together (VLM processors handle image token expansion)
        const inputs = await this.processor(preparedImages, text);

        // Run model
        const output = await this.model.generate({
            ...inputs,
            ...generate_kwargs,
        });

        // Decode output
        const decoded = this.tokenizer.batch_decode(/** @type {Tensor} */(output), {
            skip_special_tokens: true,
        });

        return decoded.map(x => ({ generated_text: x.trim() }));
    }
}
```

**Design notes:**
- Uses `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs` (tokenizer + processor + model) — matching the
  multimodal pipeline pattern.
- Calls `this.processor(preparedImages, text)` together so VLM processors can correctly
  expand image tokens inside the text prompt (e.g. LLaVA's `<image>` → N tokens).
- Spreads `...inputs` into `model.generate()` — this passes `pixel_values`, `input_ids`,
  and `attention_mask` as a single call, which is how `AutoModelForImageTextToText` models
  (using `imageTextToTextForward` at line 819 of models.js) expect their inputs.
- Uses `this.tokenizer.batch_decode()` (not `this.processor.batch_decode()`) — same as
  `ImageToTextPipeline`, because the pipeline has a named `tokenizer` component.

---

### Step 4 — Register in `SUPPORTED_TASKS`

In the `SUPPORTED_TASKS` object (starting at line 3096), add the new task entry after the
`"image-to-text"` entry (after line 3255). Placement next to the other image/multimodal
tasks keeps the object logically grouped:

```js
"image-text-to-text": {
    "tokenizer": AutoTokenizer,
    "pipeline": ImageTextToTextPipeline,
    "model": AutoModelForImageTextToText,
    "processor": AutoProcessor,
    "default": {
        "model": "onnx-community/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct",
    },
    "type": "multimodal",
},
```

---

### Step 5 — Update the `pipeline()` JSDoc task list

The `pipeline()` factory function (line 3446) has a JSDoc `@param` block listing all
supported tasks (lines 3418–3441). Add the new entry to keep docs accurate:

```js
 *  - `"image-text-to-text"`: will return a `ImageTextToTextPipeline`.
```

Insert it alphabetically, near `"image-to-text"`.

---

### Step 6 — Create the test file

Create `tests/pipelines/test_pipelines_image_text_to_text.js`. The test runner in
`tests/test_utils.js` (line 121) auto-discovers all files in `tests/pipelines/` — no
registration is needed.

```js
import { pipeline, ImageTextToTextPipeline } from "../../src/transformers.js";

import { MAX_MODEL_LOAD_TIME, MAX_TEST_EXECUTION_TIME, MAX_MODEL_DISPOSE_TIME, DEFAULT_MODEL_OPTIONS } from "../init.js";
import { load_cached_image } from "../asset_cache.js";

const PIPELINE_ID = "image-text-to-text";

export default () => {
  describe("Image Text To Text", () => {
    const model_id = "hf-internal-testing/tiny-random-LlavaForConditionalGeneration";
    /** @type {ImageTextToTextPipeline} */
    let pipe;
    let image;
    beforeAll(async () => {
      pipe = await pipeline(PIPELINE_ID, model_id, DEFAULT_MODEL_OPTIONS);
      image = await load_cached_image("white_image");
    }, MAX_MODEL_LOAD_TIME);

    it("should be an instance of ImageTextToTextPipeline", () => {
      expect(pipe).toBeInstanceOf(ImageTextToTextPipeline);
    });

    describe("batch_size=1", () => {
      it(
        "default",
        async () => {
          const output = await pipe(image, "Describe this image.");
          expect(output).toBeInstanceOf(Array);
          expect(output[0]).toHaveProperty("generated_text");
          expect(typeof output[0].generated_text).toBe("string");
        },
        MAX_TEST_EXECUTION_TIME,
      );
    });

    afterAll(async () => {
      await pipe.dispose();
    }, MAX_MODEL_DISPOSE_TIME);
  });
};
```

> **Note:** The test model ID `hf-internal-testing/tiny-random-LlavaForConditionalGeneration`
> needs to be verified to exist on the Hub. If unavailable, substitute the closest available
> tiny ONNX-compatible VLM from `hf-internal-testing` (e.g. a PaliGemma or SmolVLM tiny).

---

## Reused Existing Patterns / Utilities

| Utility | File | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `prepareImages()` | `src/pipelines.js` line 91 | Normalises image inputs to `RawImage[]` |
| `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs` typedef | `src/pipelines.js` line 215 | Constructor type for tokenizer+processor pipelines |
| `AutoModelForImageTextToText` | `src/models.js` line 8736 | Auto-loads any mapped VLM |
| `AutoProcessor` | already imported in pipelines.js | Loads the model-specific multimodal processor |
| `AutoTokenizer` | already imported in pipelines.js | Loads the model's tokenizer for decoding |

---

## What NOT to change

- `src/transformers.js` — already does `export * from './models.js'` and
  `export * from './pipelines.js'`; new exports flow through automatically.
- Any existing pipeline class — the task explicitly forbids modifying existing pipelines.
- `src/models.js` — `AutoModelForImageTextToText` is already defined and exported.

---

## Verification

1. **Unit test:** Run `npm test -- --testPathPattern pipelines` to execute the new test.
2. **Manual smoke test:**
   ```js
   import { pipeline } from '@huggingface/transformers';
   const pipe = await pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'onnx-community/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct');
   const out = await pipe('https://huggingface.co/datasets/Xenova/transformers.js-docs/resolve/main/cats.jpg', 'What is in this image?');
   console.log(out); // [{ generated_text: '...' }]
   await pipe.dispose();
   ```
3. **instanceof check:** `pipe instanceof ImageTextToTextPipeline` should be `true`.
4. **Task listing:** `SUPPORTED_TASKS['image-text-to-text']` should return the registration
   object with `pipeline: ImageTextToTextPipeline`.

